The error `Error: A datasource block is missing in the Prisma schema file` indicates that the `server/schema.prisma` file is incomplete. It needs the configuration telling Prisma to use SQLite.

I am also updating `server/index.ts` to include the **full list of products** (Accounts, Social Media, etc.) for the seeding process, as the current file in your project contains a simplified version ("...Copie des donn√©es...").

### Instructions:
1.  **Update the files** below.
2.  Run `npx prisma db push` inside the `server` folder.
3.  Run `npm start` (or `npx ts-node index.ts`) inside the `server` folder.

# Updated files:

## server/schema.prisma

Added the missing `generator` and `datasource` blocks required for Prisma to work with SQLite.

```prisma
// This is your Prisma schema file

generator client {
  provider = "prisma-client-js"
}

datasource db {
  provider = "sqlite"
  url      = "file:./dev.db"
}

model User {
  id               String   @id @default(uuid())
  username         String
  email            String   @unique
  password         String
  role             String   @default("USER") // GUEST, USER, AGENT, ADMIN
  balance          Float    @default(0.0)
  avatarUrl        String   @default("")
  subscriptionTier String   @default("Free") // Free, Pro, Elite
  createdAt        DateTime @default(now())
  orders           Order[]
}

model Listing {
  id                String   @id @default(uuid())
  game              String
  title             String
  description       String
  price             Float
  type              String   // ListingType enum stored as string
  subCategory       String?
  stock             Int
  deliveryTimeHours Int
  imageUrl          String
  createdAt         DateTime @default(now())
}

model Order {
  id              String   @id @default(uuid())
  userId          String
  listingId       String
  status          String   @default("PAID_PROCESSING")
  amount          Float
  listingSnapshot String   // JSON string of the listing at time of purchase
  createdAt       DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt       DateTime @updatedAt
  user            User     @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
}
```

